&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial, serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;en-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Savini- When tradition meets innovation&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;en-US&quot;&gt;Since 1867, in the Galleria Vittorio Emanuele and between the Teatro alla Scala and the Duomo Cathedral, the Savini Restaurant is one of the most historic restaurants in Milan and has become the symbol of the city of Milan.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;en-US&quot;&gt;At the beginning of &amp;#8216;900, when the gallery had become the focal point of social life and the Milanese music scene, the restaurant Savini becomes a privileged meeting place for artists, intellectuals, writers and characters of the opera world. Among the famous people who inspired and dined at Savini in those years are: Giuseppe Verdi, Giacomo Puccini, Giovanni Verga, Gabriele D&amp;#8217;Annunzio, Arturo Toscanini, Toto, Henry Ford, Maria Callas and Grace Kelly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;en-US&quot;&gt;It is said that in the private rooms of the restaurant, Tommaso Marinetti gave birth to the Futurist movement by writing the famous Manifesto here. The history of Savini joins the modernity represented by the open kitchen and Executive Chef&rsquo;s John Bon&rsquo;s creative menu. His recipes perfectly express his philosophy; His dish of smoked Norway lobster, stuffed with chocolate guanava and fresh broad beans, with transparency of shellfish consomm&eacute; with saffron, is a dish that externalizes his love for the raw materials of excellence and the significant stages of his career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial, serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;en-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Additional DETAILS:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
